keystone.api.wrappers.blocks

Class BlockPalette

  • java.lang.Object
    • keystone.api.wrappers.blocks.BlockPalette

  • public class BlockPalette
extends java.lang.Object
    A weighted palette of Blocks for a filter. Used to set a block to a random state from a list

      • with

        public BlockPalette with(java.lang.String block)
        Add a block ID to the palette. Any ID that is a valid ID for the /setblock command will work. Add a number to the end to specify the block's weight in the palette, with a higher weight being more likely to be chosen. [e.g. "minecraft:stone_slab[type=top] 10"]
        Parameters:
        block - The block ID and optional weight
        Returns:
        The modified BlockPalette

      • without

        public BlockPalette without(java.lang.String block)
        Remove a block ID from the palette. Any ID that is a valid ID for the /setblock command will work. Add a number to the end to specify the weight to remove from the block in the palette instead of automatically removing it. [e.g. "minecraft:stone_slab[type=top] 10"]
        Parameters:
        block - The block ID and optional weight
        Returns:
        The modified BlockPalette

      • without

        public BlockPalette without(java.lang.String block,
                            int weight)
        Remove weight from a block in the palette. Any ID that is a valid ID for the /setblock command will work. If the remaining weight is zero or less, the entry will be removed. [e.g. "minecraft:stone_slab[type=top] 10"]
        Parameters:
        block - The block ID
        weight - The weight to remove
        Returns:
        The modified BlockPalette
